## Commands
- Dev: `pnpm dev`
- Build: `pnpm build`
- Test: `pnpm test`
- Lint: `pnpm lint`
- DB migrate: `pnpm db:push`

## Conventions
- Conventional commits (enforced by commit-msg hook)
- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only at leaves that need state/effects/browser APIs
- All AI calls go through `lib/ai/`; never client-side
- Env vars defined in `src/env.js` via `@t3-oss/env-nextjs`

## What NOT to do
- Don't add packages without discussion
- Don't use Pages Router
- Don't put AI calls client-side
- Don't commit `.env` or any file containing secrets
- Don't bypass commit hooks (`--no-verify`)

## Common pitfalls
- T3 picks Biome OR ESLint at init — do not add the other; they fight
- Drizzle migrations live in `drizzle/`; never edit them by hand after generation
- Tailwind v4 needs the codemod if you upgrade from v3
